<A>__{hanna and the prisoners are led into the court. hanna's suit is so formal that members of the public call out. `nazi! nazi!' dieter leans in to marthe. hanna walks on to her place.}
<L>__{interior courtroom. day}
<A>__{everyone rises as the judges come in to take their places. hanna's face is resigned, without expression. the judges sit. the whole court goes quiet.}
<C>__{judge}
<D>__{the court finds guilty the defendants rita beckhart, karolina steinhof, regina kreutz, angela zieber, andrea luhmann jointly aiding and abetting murder in three hundred cases. the court finds the defendant hanna schmitz guilty of murder in three hundred cases.}
<A>__{there are tears in michael's eyes as he watches.}
<C>__{judge}
<D>__{the court sentences the accused as follows. rita beckhart, karolina steinhof, regina kreutz, angela zieber, and andrea luhmann, you will each serve a total sentence in prison of four years and three months.}
<A>__{rohl, marthe, dieter and the students are looking down on the sentencing. michael is crying.}
<C>__{judge}
<D>__{hanna schmitz, in view of your own admissions and your special role, you are in a different category. the court sentences the accused schmitz to imprisonment for life.}
<A>__{hanna is impassive, not reacting. then she turns and looks up to the gallery.}
